0 "" {TEXT -1 29 "Note:  Also, the the command " }{TEXT 293 6 "coeffs
" }{TEXT -1 15 " unfortunately " }{TEXT 294 8 "does not" }{TEXT -1 36 
" pick off the coefficients in order." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "The " }{TEXT 260 16 "Binomial Theorem
" }{TEXT -1 66 " gives a formula for finding the coefficients of the e
xpansion of " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)^n;" "6#),&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&%\"nG
" }{TEXT -1 10 "  for any " }{TEXT 295 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 53 ".  It is re
latively obvious that the coefficient of  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "a^k*b^(n-k
);" "6#*&)%\"aG%\"kG\"\"\")%\"bG,&%\"nGF'F&!\"\"F'" }{TEXT -1 19 "  fo
r any value of " }{TEXT 296 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 11 " from 0 to " }{TEXT 
297 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 46 " is given by the number of ways we can choose \+
" }{TEXT 298 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 8 " of the " }{TEXT 300 1 "a" }{TEXT -1 
12 "'s from the " }{TEXT 299 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 1 " " }{TEXT 301 1 "a" }
{TEXT -1 20 "'s in the expansion " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(a+b)*(a+b)" "6#*&,
&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF&F&,&F%F&F'F&F&" }{TEXT -1 7 " ....( " }{XPPEDIT 18 
0 "(a+b)" "6#,&%\"aG\"\"\"%\"bGF%" }{TEXT -1 4 " ), " }{TEXT 302 1 "n
" }{TEXT -1 41 " times .   The number of combinations of " }{TEXT 303 
1 "n" }{TEXT -1 18 " objects choosing " }{TEXT 304 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 12 
" at a time, " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "nCk" "6#%$nCkG" }{TEXT -1 27 ", is give
n by the formula  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "nCk=n!/(k!*(n-k)!)" "6#/%$nCkG*&-%
*factorialG6#%\"nG\"\"\"*&-F'6#%\"kGF*-F'6#,&F)F*F.!\"\"F*F2" }{TEXT 
-1 2 " ." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 262 
10 "State the " }{TEXT 261 16 "Binomial Theorem" }{TEXT -1 1 " " }
{TEXT 305 31 "and use Maple to demonstrate it" }{TEXT -1 1 "." }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT 323 0 "" }{TEXT 324 93 "The Binom
ial Theorem is a theorem giving the expansion of a binomial raised to \+
a given power." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 8 "Compute " }{XPPEDIT 18 
0 "sum(binomial(n,k),k=0..n)" "6#-%$sumG6$-%)binomialG6$%\"nG%\"kG/F*;
\"\"!F)" }{TEXT -1 34 "  for n=1 to 10.  Here the symbol " }{XPPEDIT 
18 0 "Sigma;" "6#%&SigmaG" }{TEXT -1 70 " (Greek letter Sigma) stands \+
for sum.   (See the worksheet SumSeq.mws)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 34 "Sum(a+b)^n,binomial(a
,b),n=1..10);" }}{PARA 8 "" 1 "" {TEXT -1 22 "Error, `)` unexpected\n
" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 259 59 "What general formula do the above c
alculations in  suggest?" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 388 "5.  Pascal's Triangle.  Recall the definition of \+
Pascal's Triangle.   Use Maple to construct the first 10 rows of Pasca
l's Triangle. (The trick will be to get the coefficients to occur in t
he correct order.  The Maple command for generating a sequence might b
e helpful. It is   seq(expression(i),i=m..n);   where expression(i) is
 an expression with index i and m..n is a range of numbers." }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG 
